      "content": "i get the professional thing but i just feel like you're not really getting what i'm saying. it's not just a \"belief system\" or \"psychometry\" stuff. it feels more like a glitch in how i'm perceiving time. like, if the vase was showing me the explosion before it happened, then time isn't just a straight line, is it? there must be a reason why i'm seeing these echoes while everyone else is just walking past them completely oblivious. do you think there's a way to actually focus on it? like, if i look at something else, can i see the next thing coming?",
